Challenge¶

Imagine you are starting a new business and you are curious to know if you should focus more on developing a mobile app or a website to sell your products?

We here have sample data of the customers from a company which have similar products.

So let's build a simple regression model to find out a more suitable platform for our new business!

Regression Model¶

Splitting dataset into training data and testing data

Let's go ahead and split the dataset into training and testing sets. We will use the training set to train our model and use testing set to test our model.

We will set the variable 'x' equal to the numerical features of the customers. These are the features we will use to see how they increase the value of Yearly Amount Spent(i.e the 'y' variable or the sales of the company)

The variable 'y' is the "Yearly Amount Spent" column. We are trying to find out how the other features contribute in increasing the yearly Amount Spent by the customers(i.e the Sales of the company)

In [168]:
X = df[['Avg. Session Length', 'Time on App','Time on Website', 'Length of Membership']]
y = df['Yearly Amount Spent']
In [169]:
X_train, X_test, y_train, y_test = train_test_split(X, y, test_size=0.3, random_state=100)
In [170]:
model = LinearRegression()
In [171]:
model.fit(X_train,y_train)

Now lets evaluate the model performance with some metrics by calculating the residual sum of squares and the explained variance score (R^2).

We will calculate the Mean Absolute Error (MAE), Mean Squared Error (MSE), and the Root Mean Squared Error (RMSE)

In [175]:
print('MAE:', metrics.mean_absolute_error(y_test, prediction))
print('MSE:', metrics.mean_squared_error(y_test, prediction))
print('RMSE:', np.sqrt(metrics.mean_squared_error(y_test, prediction)))

Conclusion¶

Okay so looks like our model is ready. Time to study the features and see how they affect the yearly amount spent by the customers

In [176]:
coeffecients = pd.DataFrame(model.coef_,X.columns)
coeffecients.columns = ['Coeffecient']
coeffecients
Out[176]:
Coeffecient
Avg. Session Length 26.155324
Time on App 38.620085
Time on Website 0.317603
Length of Membership 61.820394

Below is what we can interpret from the coefficient of our model.

  1. Avg. Session Length increases the Yearly Amount Spent by almost 26 units
  2. Time on App increases the Yearly Amount Spent by 38 units
  3. Time on Website increases the Yearly Amount Spent by 0.3 units
  4. Length of Membership increases the Yearly Amount Spent by 61 units

We can conclude that the time spent on the App is more correlated to the customer's yearly expenditure and it is evident that we should focus more on building the app to draw more business from the customers.

We also noticed that the Lenght of the Membership correlates to yearly amount spend even more! Well it would be a good idea if in future we explore on how we can work on increasing the length of membership to increase customer's yearly spent amount.

Comclusion: Mobile App it is!
